Text: How long does it hurt for?

The shot is a type of birth control that you get every 3 months to prevent pregnancy. It’s technically called DepoProvera and it works by preventing ovulation (when your body releases an egg) - no egg, no baby! If you don’t mind getting a quick prick every 3 months, you should definitely talk to your doctor about getting it.
